{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "09", "m": "11", "Y": "2025"}, "time": {"H": "18", "M": "12", "S": "41"}}, "news": [{"title": "Rajkot civic body crosses 50% of year\u2019s property tax collection target", "para": "Rajkot Municipal Corporation has reached 50% of its annual property tax target, collecting Rs 301.03 crore. Incentives include rebates for early payment and additional discounts for online transactions. The RMC is also actively sealing properties of defaulters and utilizing WhatsApp for efficient bill delivery and payment.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/rajkot-municipal-corporation-hits-50-of-property-tax-target-amid-digital-innovations/125202133?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-90148/125202133.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Centre orders probe into PMAY housing project for CRZ violations in Kharghar", "para": "The Union environment ministry has directed Maharashtra to investigate alleged Coastal Regulation Zone (CRZ) violations in a Navi Mumbai PMAY housing project. Environmental groups complain the construction is too close to mangroves and the high-tide line, posing climate risks. The ministry asked the state coastal authority to examine the matter and take action if violations are confirmed.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/probe-launched-into-pmay-housing-project-in-kharghar-for-crz-violations/125201539?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-77906/125201539.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Major relief for Delhi Development Authority in housing project case", "para": "Delhi's Real Estate Appellate Tribunal (REAT) overturned a Rs 1 crore penalty against the Delhi Development Authority (DDA) for failing to register a housing project. REAT ruled that the Rohini project was completed before RERA's establishment in 2017, making registration unnecessary. The tribunal sent the case back to RERA for a review of the complaint.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/rera/delhi-development-authority-wins-appeal-rs-1-crore-penalty-overturned-in-housing-project-dispute/125201516?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-107800/125201516.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "rera"}]}